{
  "texts": [
    "1: Two-layer hierarchical feedback control scheme based on reinforcement learning, adapted from [12].",
    "Each herder H i,j detects the positions of other agents and determines the target T * i,j via a target-selection heuristic.",
    "The corresponding motion is then governed by the driving policy, which outputs the velocity command u of the herder.where I A (q) is the indicator function of set A, equal to 1 if q ∈ A and 0 otherwise.",
    "The first term keeps the herder close to the target, the second pushes the target toward the goal region Ω G, and the third penalizes large control actions.",
    "The gains are chosen such that k s > k a > k c.To promote obstacle-aware behavior, we employ a simple curriculum on the initial conditions."
  ]
}